explanation:
OS_OBJECT_TABLE_GET -- This macro is used to fetch the sem object. It may expand to code or a call that performs comparisons (or invokes OS_ObjectIndexFromToken); the macro expansion must be inspected to see if memcmp is used to compare token contents (and specifically null-terminated strings).

OS_impl_bin_sem_table -- The object table referenced by the macro. Its implementation/contents (e.g., key fields or lookup code) may include string fields or comparison logic that could use memcmp on null-terminated strings.

OS_impl_binsem_internal_record_t -- Type of the returned "sem" object. Its definition must be checked for any string members or helper routines associated with it that might perform memcmp on null-terminated strings.

OS_object_token_t -- The token type passed into the macro. If this token is or contains a null-terminated string (or is compared as such), code that handles it may use memcmp incorrectly; the token definition is needed to determine whether comparisons constitute string comparisons.

OS_ObjectIndexFromToken -- This function is listed as a callee in the static graph and is commonly used in object-table lookups. Its implementation must be inspected because it could call memcmp (or otherwise compare strings) when matching tokens.

memcmp -- The standard library function whose use is forbidden by the MISRA rule for comparing null-terminated strings. The analysis must search for direct or indirect uses of memcmp in the above symbols (macro expansions, table code, token/index functions) to determine whether the target function (including code it expands/calls) violates the rule.
